ml_deployment/
│
├── myvirtualenv/                # Virtual environment folder (auto-created)
│   ├── bin/                     # Contains Python executable for this environment
│   ├── lib/                     # Installed libraries
│   └── ...                      # Other files for venv management
│
├── app/                         # Your application folder
│   ├── train_model.py           # Your training script
│   └── other_scripts.py         # Other Python scripts
│
├── data/                        # Data folder (e.g., datasets, processed data)
│   ├── train.csv
│   ├── test.csv
│   └── ...
│
├── models/                      # Saved models (e.g., pickle or joblib files)
│   ├── model.pkl
│   └── ...
│
├── requirements.txt             # List of dependencies
└── README.md                    # Project documentation


Step 1: Set up a new environment
python -m venv myvirtualenv

Step 2: Make sure you are in the virtual environment
source myvirtualenv/bin/activate

Step 3: Create the requirements.txt file and fill it out with the following library list.
pandas
scikit-learn
fastapi
pydantic
uvicorn
streamlit

Step 4: After the requirements.txt ready, we must install them using the following code.
pip install -r requirements.txt

Step 5: Create a 'data' folder under the myvirtualenv folder. Then download  the diabetes data from Kaggle (https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/uciml/pima-indians-diabetes-database)
